# Trivy ignore file — documented, justified vulnerability exceptions.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Only add a CVE here after reviewing it and
# deciding it is a false positive or an accepted risk (e.g. not reachable in
# our code path). Each entry MUST have a justification comment.
#
# Example (leave commented until a real, reviewed case exists):
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # base-image OpenSSL advisory, not exploitable — no TLS server code; tracked, awaiting node:20-alpine patch.
